  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ 425°F/ Gas 7</p>\n<p>Boil a kettle</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>tortiglioni</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\n<p>Cook the<strong> tortiglioni</strong> for 8-10 min or until cooked with a slight <span class=\"text-highlight\">bite and once done, drain the <strong>tortiglioni</strong>, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></span></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1756.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1756.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1756.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1756.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1756.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop the <strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 30g <span class=\"text-danger\">[60g]</span><strong> butter</strong> over a medium heat</p>\n<p>Once melted, add the <strong>chopped onion</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1756.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1756.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1756.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1756.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1756.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, drain the <strong>tuna</strong></p>\n<p>Drain the<strong> sweetcorn</strong></p>\n<p>Grate the <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>\n<p>Combine the <strong>grated cheddar</strong> with the <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> and <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> in a small bowl – this is your<strong> cheesy topping</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1756.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1756.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1756.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1756.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1756.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add 30g <span class=\"text-danger\">[60g]</span> <strong>flour</strong> to the pan and stir with a wooden spoon for 1 min or until the onion is fully coated in the flour</p>\n<p>Gradually whisk 350ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [700ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong> into the pan, a little at a time and cook for 5 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains – this is your <strong>béchamel sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1756.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1756.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1756.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1756.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1756.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> Dijon mustard</strong> to the <strong>béchamel sauce</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>\n<p>Add the <strong>drained tortiglioni</strong> to the<strong> béchamel sauce</strong> with the <strong>drained tuna</strong> and<strong> sweetcorn</strong></p>\n<p>Add a splash of <strong>starchy pasta water</strong> and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>pasta mixture</strong></p>\n<p>Tip: add enough water so that it <span class=\"text-highlight\">feels saucy, as this</span> will continue to thicken in the oven!</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1756.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1756.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1756.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1756.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1756.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Transfer the <strong>pasta mixture</strong> to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> and sprinkle over the <strong>cheesy topping</strong></p>\n<p>Put the dish in the oven for 15 min or until bubbling and golden</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
